# Lecture 05 – Cookies & JWT (Backend)


This project demonstrates how Cookies and JWT authentication
work in a Node.js and Express backend application.


## Folder Structure
Lecture_05_cookies_jwt
├── 01_cookies
├── 02_JWT

## Features
- Setting cookies in Express
- Reading cookies using cookie-parser
- JWT creation and verification
- Storing JWT in HTTP-only cookies
- Protecting routes using JWT


## Tech Stack
- Node.js
- Express.js
- Cookie Parser
- JSON Web Token (JWT)


## How to Run

```bash
npm install
nodemon api.js



Agar multiple folders hain:
```md
cd 01_cookies
npm install
nodemon api.js


## API Routes
| Method | Route | Description |
|------|------|------------|
| GET | /sign | Generate JWT |
| GET | /verify | Verify JWT |



## Output
- JWT stored in browser cookies
- Successful token verification

